y (NUE) were also initiated through a FQRNT postdoctoral fellowship to Frederic Pitre (from Canada). To investigate the possible link between biomass production (i.e. yield) and NUE, a subset of 12 genotypes of K8, including the yield extremes, was selected for a pot experiment designed to follow the seasonal cycling of nutrient at the whole plant level. The carbon and nitrogen budget is being documented as well as the allocation and partition of compounds using stable isotopes (13C and 15N). Data from this experiment will provide useful background for the breeding programme.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The current controversies over biofuels from crops are mostly centred around the use of first generation food crops. The development of perennial biomass crops would provide more sustainable alternatives.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>D7F0ED1C-EF3A-4019-87BF-9A5F4F9C1ED3</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>544ce6e5824648.90714658</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Agriculture, Food and Drink,Energy,Environment</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>6D7D887F-3FE5-44B8-9EBE-9CE57EA31383</gtr:id><gtr:title>Overcoming barriers to crossing in willow (Salix spp.) breeding.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Aspects of Applied Biology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/afa2d94f6a93bb96fdac18b4fdbcbd86"><gtr:id>afa2d94f6a93bb96fdac18b4fdbcbd86</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Macalpine W</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2008-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>5450caf9b2ac53.59015155</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>F2DB3F61-DBE1-4732-AA34-5D2C8BA7E0AF</gtr:id><gtr:title>Biomass Now - Sustainable Growth and U